org.openimaj.image.text.extraction

Class TextExtractor<T extends Image<?,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.text.extraction.TextExtractor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of Image
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageProcessor<T>, Processor<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LiuSamarabanduTextExtractorBasic, LiuSamarabanduTextExtractorMultiscale

    public abstract class TextExtractor<T extends Image<?,T>>
extends Object
implements ImageProcessor<T>
    An interface for classes that are able to extract text from images. The single method allows the retrieval of the text mapped to the bounding boxes of the text within the image.

    Note that this is an ImageProcessor extension so that the TextExtractor should process the image prior to the getTextRegions() method being called.

    This class will deal with the processing of extracted text regions with the OCR processor. Use setOCRProcessor(OCRProcessor) to choose with OCR processor will be used on the extracted regions.

    Author:
    David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

    • Method Detail

      • getTextRegions

        public abstract Map<Rectangle,T> getTextRegions()
        Get the text regions that can be extracted from an image. The images in the values of the map need not be simply the extracted region that is bounded by the rectangular key (this can be done afterwards), but may be a representation that is as near to canonical as possible - that is, it may be warped or thresholded such that an OCR processor may have less trouble reading the text
        Returns:
        A map from bounding box in original image to a canonical representation of the text (may be warped or thresholded)

      • getText

        public Map<Rectangle,IndependentPair<T,String>> getText()
        Get text that can be extracted from an image. The map should map a bounding box within the processed image to a pair of extracted image vs. text string. The extracted image may not necessarily be the region of interest which the rectangle bounds; it can be as close to a canonical representation of the text as possible such that an OCR would have less difficulty in classifying the text. For example, the image may be thresholded or warped such that the text is straight.
        Returns:
        A map of bounding box to a pair of image and text string

      • getTextStrings

        public List<String> getTextStrings()
        If you're not interested in where the strings are located in the image you can use this method to simply get a list of extracted strings.
        Returns:
        A List of strings extracted from the image.

      • setOCRProcessor

        public void setOCRProcessor(OCRProcessor<T> ocr)
        For the text regions that are extracted to be associated with textual representations of the text regions, an OCR processor must be used. Use this function to choose which OCR processor is used to extract read text regions.
        Parameters:
        ocr - The OCRProcessor to use
